l_viewer - a simple L-system viewer
==========================

pre-requirements
-----------------

this script is written in python. install 'python' and 'Tkinter'
to run the script. (use synaptic package manager in Ubuntu
to install them)

how to run
-----------

to run the application we need a text file containing the
L-system information. the format of the file is like this.

axiom
starting angle
angle
number of rules
rule1
rule2
......
......
number of symbols with actions
symble1=action1,action2
symbol2=action3
......
......

you only have to mension the symbols(variables & constances) with actions 
in here. actions avilable are,

L - turn left
R - turn right
P - push
O - pop
F - move forword

example1:

XY
0.0
90.0
2
X=X+YF
Y=FX-Y
3
+=L
-=R
F=F

example2:

0
0.0
45.0
2
1=11
0=1[0]0
4
[=P,L
]=O,R
0=F
1=F

there are few info files supplied with the application.

then use fallowing commnand to run the application

python viewer.py

then you need to load the info file. use load button to do it.
the press start. you can move around and zoom the view but pause
befoure doing that. and try to do the moving and zooming when
it is in gone only 4 or 5 genarations.

